Male, 40 - 59 years

Age Reported Symptoms Notes
40 2021-01-04 rash with redness, rash At about 1330 on 30DEC, the patient received the 1st dose of the Moderna COVID-19 vaccine. Less tha... Read more
Close
At about 1330 on 30DEC, the patient received the 1st dose of the Moderna COVID-19 vaccine. Less than five minutes after the vaccine was administered, the patient noticed a metallic taste. About two to three minutes afterwards, the patient noticed a ?tingling? sensation mostly on the left side of the face and minimally on the right side. Almost immediately after the ?tingling? sensation, the patient felt the sensation of an increased heart rate and checked his pulse with his watch that had a pulse sensor. The watch indicated that he had a heart rate of 115 bpm. This sensation of an increased heart rate subsided after for one or two minutes and repeat pulse measurement was in the low 90s. Towards the end of the 15 minute post-vaccination observation period, the medical technician did the final check on the patient. The patient admitted to experiencing a metallic taste and a mild tingling sensation on the neck and face area. The service member was immediately brought back to the treatment room were a faint red rash and was noticed on the left side of the neck by the medical providers present. Two doses of Benadryl 25mg were given and the patient was told to continue to be observed in the observation area. After about 20 minutes, the tingling sensation resolved. The patient checked his pulse again and it was in the low 70s. The metallic taste resolved after about one and a half hours after the start of the symptom.

1414- 18min after injection Patient stated he was feeling funny. He reported feeling hot and discomfort to Left side of his neck. Upon evaluation he was mildly tachycardic HR 110. Symptoms began to worsen with redness spreading through his hands and upper torso and pt became diaphoretic. by 1420 Pt BP increased to 171/104. Pt was given IM Benadryl and Decadron per Dr. orders. by 1440 redness had completely resolved and Diaphoresis was gone, HR down to 144/82. by 1500 all Pt's symptoms resolved. Pt was able to be discharged from clinic without s/sx of distress.

The shot was administered in my left arm. I experienced localized swelling and axillary lymph node tenderness immediately after injection under my left armpit. The right side of my face also became numb for about 5 minutes. The next morning the areas around my eyes were swollen and I had two styes in my right eye. I do not know if these were related. These symptoms lasted approximately 3 days. Some minimal swelling and tenderness seemed to remain, and approximately a week later I experienced a painful resurgence of the swelling at the injection site that was far larger, harder and more painful. I took Benadryl and Ibuprofen. These relieved the symptoms within 48 hours.

40 2021-01-27 shingles, injection site pain Initially, no immediate problems other than slightly tender at injection site. Approximately 48 hour... Read more
Close
Initially, no immediate problems other than slightly tender at injection site. Approximately 48 hours later (evening 01/14/2021) started to notice increased inflammation about the size of a "quarter" on left side of chin. I did have a pimple/ingrown hair at this site prior to the injection which was mostly healed but not entirely healed. The next morning, 01/15/2021, I experience mild facial numbness to the left side of my chin and mild facial paralysis resulting in an asymmetrical smile, and mild swelling to the left side of my face. Two day later (morning 01/17/2021) with my symptoms not worsening but showing only a little improvement, I went to my local urgent care for evaluation. Provider was not 100% sure of the diagnosis but felt this could be a case of shingles or folliculitis. I was treated with a 7 day course of acyclovir and a 10 day course of doxycycline hyclate. The numbness subsided 2-3 days after treatment began. The facial paralysis and swelling showed much improvement (90-95%) after completing the acyclovir on 01/24/2021; however, I feel there is still a little more improvement to go.

Within one minute of receiving vaccine, the patient became pale, stated that he felt dizzy and fainted. Patient regained consciousness within one minute. Upon regaining consciousness, patient reported feeling lightheaded and dizzy but was oriented to person, place and time. Skin was warm and dry but pale in color. After regaining consciousness, patient also stated that he has a history of fainting 5-6 years ago after receiving an influenza vaccination. (During screening questions, patient denied having any reactions to vaccines in the past) Patient independently moved from a chair to a laying down position on a cot and expressed an improvement in how he was feeling. Vital signs taken after event as recorded below. When asked patient stated that he does recall times when he thinks he may have been hypoglycemic in the past. Patient also states that he has been very nervous about receiving injections throughout his life. EMS called and assessed patient at the vaccination clinic site. Patient drank a 10 oz bottle of orange juice prior to EMS arriving and when EMS staff obtained his blood sugar the result was 97. EMS stated that patient was stable and all vital signs were stable. Patients skin color improved to pink. Patients wife was called by patient and she provided transportation home for patient. Prior to leaving the vaccination clinic, patient was walking around for several minutes and denied any feelings of being lightheaded or dizzy. 40 2021-03-16 injection site pain It has been 6 weeks since my 2nd dose of the Moderna vaccine for Covid-19. For the first 3-4 days I ... Read more
Close
It has been 6 weeks since my 2nd dose of the Moderna vaccine for Covid-19. For the first 3-4 days I had the usual moderate flu-like symptoms: dizziness, headaches, fatigue, chills, soreness at vaccine siteetc. Days 5-7 I seemed to gradually improve. On day 8 all of the symptoms returned with greater severity: this time I had a fever, the chills were much more intense, the headaches were excruciating, body and joint aches all over the place--I couldn't sleep or focus on anything cognitively taxing. Interestingly, my brother, who was vaccinated just after me, also had more severe side effects beginning on day 8 post 2nd dose. He improved after 3-4 days, but my recovery has been much much lengthier. By day 14 I was still feeling very ill, though the fever did subside. Sometime in the third week the pain in my arm at the vaccination site returned, then became intermittent, and still bothers me from time to time. I also started getting muscle spasms in the same exact locations that sent me to the ER after my probably bout with Covid in the spring of 2020. Thankfully these lasted only a week or so, though I began feeling muscle soreness in different parts of my body, ever changing. By the 4th week I was slightly better and down to 4 main symptoms: chills (by far the worst of the symptoms--to the point at which my skin would feel like it was being frostbitten by dry ice every time I changed sweaty clothes), occasional splitting headaches, and muscle soreness that included both the injection site on my arm and other areas. I had other symptoms as well, fatigue and brain fog, etc, but these were present before the vaccination, though not as severe.

I began feeling soreness at the injection site started within 12 hours of receiving the vax. The soreness progressively became worse over the next 7-9 days and was accompanied by swelling of the muscle around the injection site (peaking at about 7 days post-injection). The discomfort at times extended down my arm, but never past my elbow. When extending my arm outwards (e.g., when reaching for something), I would feel an unusual stiffness and moderate discomfort in my arm. As of April 12 (13 days post-vax), the swelling is largely gone, but there is still some discomfort when extending my arm outwards. In addition, there appear to be dry patches of skin between the injection site and my armpit. I have not sought medical treatment for these adverse reactions to date, nor do I anticipate needing to unless the discomfort becomes more intense.

The occurrence of additional non-serious events is detailed below. The patient's past medical history included Chronic fatigue syndrome, Fibromyalgia and Neurocardiogenic syncope. On 13-Jan-2021, the patient received first dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) 1 dosage form. On 10-Feb-2021, received second dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) dosage was changed to 1 dosage form. On 01-Feb-2021, the patient experienced DIZZINESS (dizzy.). On 10-Feb-2021, the patient experienced ARTHRALGIA (joint pains), CHILLS (chills) and PYREXIA (mild fever). In February 2021, the patient experienced FEELING ABNORMAL ("feels like my body has been split into 1000 different microclimates). On 18-Feb-2021, the patient experienced ARRHYTHMIA (arrhythmias) (seriousness criterion medically significant), PAROSMIA (altered smell), PALPITATIONS (heart rhythm, palpitations), TACHYCARDIA (tachycardia), PHOTOSENSITIVITY REACTION (become sensitive to light and cannot go outside without sunglasses), HYPERHIDROSIS (sweating more especially acidic and disgusting), HEADACHE (splitting headaches) and VACCINATION SITE PAIN (pain in the left arm at the vaccination site). Patient is a 41 y.o. male on no AC/AP with no pmhx reported presents 1/31 PM initially to Hospital for acute onset 10/10 headache refractory to 800mg motrin which started in occipital region then spread to whole head and neck, nausea and vomiting x 3. Symptoms started around 5pm when he was on a conference call and reports he got bad news so was stressed out. Denies any recent trauma. Pt received toradol 30mg, dexamethasone 10mg, benadryl 25mg and reglan 10mg at hospital prior to transfer. CT showed diffuse SAH and CTA showed no signs of obvious aneurysms. He then received 1g IV keppra and was started on Cardene for BP goal <140. He was transferred to NICU for further monitoring. While in the NICU, his exam and imaging remained stable. He underwent CTA which was unrevealing, and DSA which showed evidence of vasculopathy. BPs came down to <160 and he came off of cardene, did not require additional meds. He was transferred to the floor. Upon transfer, he had another thunderclap HA, accompanied by HTN to the 200s systolic, tachycardia to the 120s, diaphoresis, and blotchy macular rash over the anterior shoulders. Imaging was negative for vasospasm or recurrent bleed, and it was felt that patient's presentation was most c/w RCVS. Trigger felt either 2/2 caffeine intake (patient reported drinking 60 oz coffee daily) vs. Sympathetic discharge syndrome such as pheochromocytoma or carcinoid syndrome. LP was performed, which revealed no nucleated cells and protein elevated in proportion to blood, which confirmed the diagnosis of RCVS. Studies were sent off to diagnose carcinoid syndrome and pheo. Patient was started on nimodipine/gabapentin with standing tylenol and PRN oxycodone for breakthrough pain. Within days, the HAs had markedly decreased in intensity. He was taken off of keppra after 1 week with stable exam and no e/o seizures. He was briefly switched from nimodipine to verapamil but switched back prior to discharge. He was discharged with outpatient followup.

42 2021-04-25 hair loss, skin irritation On 4/22/21, approximately 1 hr after the Moderna COVID-19 first vaccination injection, I started to ... Read more
Close
On 4/22/21, approximately 1 hr after the Moderna COVID-19 first vaccination injection, I started to encounter allergic reactions that I used to suffer about 20 years ago. My air intake decreased, and my skin began to become irritated. I formerly had environmental allergies that would reduce my air intake, and the first place I noticed the effects were on my skin and I would become irritable. Physicians told me that when my oxygen levels were low, the body would channel the air to where it was most needed, which is generally not the skin, so my skin would become irritated. When this used to occur, I would respond involuntarily with facial twitches and pulling at my face and hair. Physicians explained that these twitches and pulling actions would draw air to the surface of my skin where I was air depleted. When I took the Moderna injection, this happened again -- I found myself with low air, my face was twitching, and I was pulling on my face to draw air to the area. The result when I was 19 and dealing with allergies is that I would remove small patches of hair from my head or eyebrows or eyelashes, and this would happen almost unconsciously as I tried to stimulate the areas and draw air to the surface of my skin. I did the same thing on 4/22/21, and found later, when looking into a mirror, that I had removed a section of my eyebrow unconsciously. It all comes back to oxygen depletion. A different and more intense event occurred in the night of Friday, 4/23/21, and the early morning of Saturday, 4/24/21. I went to bed at about 11 p.m. or 11:30 p.m. Between that time and approximately 1:30 a.m., I had difficulty sleeping, and I dreamed of pain in my chest. I finally woke up about 1:30 a.m. and found the pain in my chest was real. I was having difficulty breathing deeply. It felt as if the lower part of my lungs (at least on one side) was solidifying or inaccessible. What I did was begin forcing myself to breathe as deeply as possible. Over a period of 30 minutes or longer, I was able to gradually reclaim the use of the deepest part of my longs. With every forced deep breath, I was able to chip away at the area that felt like it was freezing up. Finally, I felt that I could access the deepest part of my longs and breath normally. The pain and lack of use in my lower lungs were very concerning.

While administering the vaccine I was sitting on a stool with wheels. The bolt had at some point become loosened and when I shifted my weight forward on the stool to administer the vaccination the wheel came off and the stool came out from underneath me. I had administered the vaccination but had not pulled the syringe from the patients arm when this happened. I landed on the floor looking up at the patient. The vaccine had been administered but the syringe was still in the patients arm. I immediately jumped up and removed the syringe. The syringe came out smoothly. The needle was not bent. I immediately placed the syringe in the sharps container per vaccination protocol. The patient did bleed. Though no more than with previous patients who have a superficial capillary nick. The patient did not move during the incident. He did not move his arm or rise or jump. He was surprised and stayed immobile. I immediately asked if he was ok and he stated he has never bled before from a vaccination. The patient stayed the requisite 20 minutes post vaccination waiting period. Before the patient left I removed the band aid to inspect the vaccination site. The area was red, but did not seem to have a tear or wound. The patient stated he felt fine.

did not get the 2nd dose (beyond day36 from 1st dose); slight fever; body chills; body aches; full body hives; This spontaneous case was reported by a patient and describes the occurrence of URTICARIA (full body hives) in a 43-year-old male patient who received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (batch no. 017B21A) for COVID-19 vaccination. The occurrence of additional non-serious events is detailed below. No Medical History information was reported. On 25-Mar-2021, the patient received first dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (unknown route) 1 dosage form. On 27-Mar-2021, the patient experienced URTICARIA (full body hives) (seriousness criterion medically significant), PYREXIA (slight fever), CHILLS (body chills) and MYALGIA (body aches). On 28-Apr-2021, the patient experienced PRODUCT DOSE OMISSION ISSUE (did not get the 2nd dose (beyond day36 from 1st dose)). The patient was treated with EPINEPHRINE ongoing since an unknown date at an unspecified dose and frequency; DIPHENHYDRAMINE, PARACETAMOL, PHENYLPROPANOLAMINE HYDROCHLORIDE (BENADRYL [DIPHENHYDRAMINE;PARACETAMOL;PHENYLPROPANOLAMINE HYDROCHLORIDE]) ongoing since an unknown date at an unspecified dose and frequency and CETIRIZINE HYDROCHLORIDE (ZYRTEC ALLERGY) ongoing since an unknown date at an unspecified dose and frequency. On 27-Mar-2021, PYREXIA (slight fever), CHILLS (body chills) and MYALGIA (body aches) had resolved. On 01-Apr-2021, URTICARIA (full body hives) had resolved. On 28-Apr-2021, PRODUCT DOSE OMISSION ISSUE (did not get the 2nd dose (beyond day36 from 1st dose)) had resolved. The action taken with mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Unknown) was unknown. In ER patient was inserted intravenous line and given Epinephrine, Benadryl, Steroids, Zyrtec as a treatment. Patient was given Benadryl and Zyrtec as home medication to take for a week. This report refers to a case of Product dose omission for mRNA-1273, and the AEs of Urticaria, Pyrexia, Chills, and Myalgia. Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the AEs, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.; Sender's Comments: This report refers to a case of Product dose omission for mRNA-1273, and the AEs of Urticaria, Pyrexia, Chills, and Myalgia. The patient's medical history was not provided. Products known to have been used by the patient, within two weeks prior to the event were not reported. On 11 Mar 2021, the patient consulted wound care for his foot and was told to be fine. On 13 Mar 2021, prior to the onset of the symptoms, the patient received their dose of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (batch number: unknown) for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On 13 Mar 2021, within eight to ten minutes, after vaccination patient felt cold .The patient's temperature was noted to be 102 degree Fahrenheit. Also, patient reported a lot of pain and discomfort. Patient also complained about chills, cold and shivering and he was given an orange juice and blanket after five to ten minutes by the pharmacist. The events sepsis and cellulitis were considered as serious (medically significant). The patient's wife reported that the patient was about to have an amputation in this past weekend. Treatment for the event included two unknown antibiotics. Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the event was unknown. Close
Note: I had a PCR confirmed SARS-CoV-2 infection in March, 2020. Approximately 12 hours after the second vaccine dose, I experienced intense soreness at the vaccination site (significantly greater than the first dose). In the middle of the night I awoke with flu-like symptoms. At 9am I took acetominophen for fever, rigors, muscle aches. This brought mild relief from approx. 9:45am to 11:15 am. My condition continued to worsen through the early afternoon with rigors and significant generalized muscle aches. I experienced tachycardia (90-105 bpm vs normal of ~70bpm), SOB, and starting measuring pulse oximetry which read from 89%-94% (my usual does not go below 97%). This persisted until approximately 8pm with no improvement. I took 40 mg prednisone, 600 mg ibuprofen and within 3 hours was starting to have symptom resolution. I am a physician and up to date on all my vaccinations. I have never had anything approaching this type of response. I don't know if prior SARS-CoV-2 infection creates a situation were the very potent mRNA vaccine triggers a large immunologic recall response. I wanted to get this noted as there may be some reason to alter the vaccine schedule for prior SARS-CoV-2 infections

I definitely had a soreness at the injection site, more than I have had with any other shot. It definitely subsided after a couple of days. Also had joint pain in my hands, elbows, and knees, and particularly in my left knee where I have arthritis, also decreased in intensity within a few days of the shot. I am not taking any antihistamines or using any topicals- just working on not scratching the area. I have read some info on the internet referring to this as "COVID Arm". It is manageable, and I am NOT deterred from getting my second shot in April.

When I got the second Covid shot, my fasting blood sugar the next two days were 147 and 143 - the highest values I have EVER recorded since I started taking insulin (earlier this year). Correspondingly, the values after lunch and dinner yesterday were very elevated. This afternoon and evening, the numbers have returned to normal, and I expect tomorrow morning's fasting value to be back around 120 again. This was not dangerous, but as an engineer, I found it to be a fascinating and statistically significant outlier. The other symptoms I had from the second shot was a fever (over 100 degrees from 11/28 5:30pm through 11/30 8am, and over 102 from 11/28 10pm through 11/29 9am), some general aches and fatigue, and injection site soreness. I had no adverse reaction to the first shot (a month earlier) except for injection site soreness.

50 2021-03-20 injection site pain I don't think that my reaction to the vaccine is super serious but it is perhaps worth noting if oth... Read more
Close
I don't think that my reaction to the vaccine is super serious but it is perhaps worth noting if others are also experiencing similar symptoms. On the second day, I did have the expected arm soreness around the injection area on my right arm. That soreness faded by Saturday morning. However, on Saturday afternoon, I began experiencing some intermittent pain in my left kidney. I have had a few (3?) kidney stones since I was approximately 35 years old so it is a pain that I recognize almost immediately. I kept my spider senses awake to see where it was going to go. About an hour later, I had intermittent "flu like" pain in my arms and legs. I had been up on a ladder painting a wall and I became a bit dizzy and decided to halt the painting project. The rest of the evening was kind of crappy. Intermittent headaches, leg pain, arm pain and left kidney pain. I took 1 Alleve tablet around 8pm. It didn't seem to do much. I took a second one about an hour later (according to the instructions you can take two for you first dose) and that seemed to do the trick! I slept like a rock and so far today, all of the pain is gone including the pain in my left kidney. I have not taken any more Alleve besides the two that I took last night. Also, as of right now (2:44pm on Sunday 3/21), no kidney stone has passed. I have been urinating into a cup to see if one comes out. I cannot 100% say that any of these symptoms are related to the vaccine. However, being a Type 1 diabetic (since 1978) and the unusual kidney pain made me go, "huh." That is why I am providing this info in the event that there are others who are experiencing similar symptoms that can be tied to the vaccine and what to expect. I feel completely fine now. Yay. :)

My fever began to subside and by Sat. morning my arm pain began to lessen and some of the swelling went down. Now Sunday morning, the fatigue, fevers and headache have gone, and most of my arm pain in gone (still tender to the touch), I still have some swelling in both upper left arm and Underarm pit. Dr. feels this was and allergic reaction and recommends I do not get the second injection.

angioedema; swollen glands below the jaw; dry mouth; canker sores; thrush; a metal taste in his mouth; swelling of lips, tongue and gums; Rash; A spontaneous report was received from a consumer concerning a 51-year-old, male patient, who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine and experienced angioedema, swollen glands below jaw, dry mouth, canker sores, thrush, metal taste in mouth, swelling of lips, tongue and gums. The patient's medical history was not provided. Concomitant product use was not provided by the reporter. 0n 06 Jan 2021, prior to the onset of symptoms, the patient received the first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Batch number: unknown) for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. The patient developed symptoms after the first dose like dry mouth, canker sores, swollen glands below the jaw, swollen tongue, thrush, a metal taste in his mouth, and swollen lips. On 05 Feb 2021, the patient received the second dose of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Batch number: unknown) for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. Nothing new happened after the second dose. On 29 Feb 2021 (the date will be confirmed) he went to ER received steroids, Benadryl and Pepcid. They treated him for angioedema. Most of the symptoms went away except for the swelling of the gums, rash and metallic taste. The outcome of the events, angioedema, swollen glands below jaw, swollen tongue and lip, dry mouth, canker sores, thrush, swelling of lips, tongue and were resolved. The outcome of the events metal taste in mouth, gums and rash were unknown.; Reporter's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

Transient ischemic Attack; Double vision; Sore injection site; Red injection site; This spontaneous case was reported by a consumer (subsequently medically confirmed) and describes the occurrence of TRANSIENT ISCHAEMIC ATTACK (Transient ischemic Attack) and DIPLOPIA (Double vision) in a 52-year-old male patient who received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (batch no. 018B21A) for COVID-19 vaccination. The occurrence of additional non-serious events is detailed below. The patient's past medical history included No adverse event (No reported medical history). On 31-Mar-2021, the patient received first dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) 1 dosage form. On 31-Mar-2021, the patient experienced VACCINATION SITE PAIN (Sore injection site) and VACCINATION SITE ERYTHEMA (Red injection site). On 02-Apr-2021, the patient experienced DIPLOPIA (Double vision) (seriousness criterion medically significant). On an unknown date, the patient experienced TRANSIENT ISCHAEMIC ATTACK (Transient ischemic Attack) (seriousness criterion medically significant). On 01-Apr-2021, VACCINATION SITE PAIN (Sore injection site) and VACCINATION SITE ERYTHEMA (Red injection site) had resolved. At the time of the report, TRANSIENT ISCHAEMIC ATTACK (Transient ischemic Attack) and DIPLOPIA (Double vision) outcome was unknown. The action taken with mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) was unknown. No concomitant medications reported by investigator. Treatment of these events included aspirin, Lipitor and Plavix. Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.; Sender's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

53 2021-04-20 rash, skin swelling, itchy skin Whole-body skin rash: Rash started on day 4 post-vaccination. It began around elbow joints and sprea... Read more
Close
Whole-body skin rash: Rash started on day 4 post-vaccination. It began around elbow joints and spread to between fingers and wrists the first day. On the next day it spread to around shoulders/armpits, groin/buttocks, hands and scalp. On subsequent days it spread to arms, torso, face, knees, ankles, legs and feet in roughly that order. Rashes began to clear from each area roughly 48-72 hours after first appearing. Over-the-counter antihistamines helped reduce puffiness of rashes and manage itchiness. Loratadine was most effective followed by Cetirizine HCl and Diphenhydramine. Over the course of the reaction, rashes spread throughout 80-90% of the surface of my skin. It is currently day 9 post-vaccination and rashes have cleared from many areas, but still remain on about 10-15% of my body.

53 2021-05-19 itchy skin, hives About 10 days after my second shot of Moderna, I experienced an outbreak of small (1-2mm), round, it... Read more
Close
About 10 days after my second shot of Moderna, I experienced an outbreak of small (1-2mm), round, itchy hives across my body. The hives were easily burst by scratching, releasing a clear fluid that scabbed over. The itching was significant. I treated it with calamine and OTC cortisone cream. New hives appeared every day for approximately ten days, after which the hives began to recede and no new hives emerged. After about 14 days the hives had mostly cleared up and the itchiness was mostly gone. Note that I was on allergen desensitization treatment (drops under the tongue every day). The day after the hives started I stopped the drops just in case that was the cause, but the hives did not get better, in fact they got worse the first few days. I was very busy with work at the time, my allergist is an hour away, and my GP was scheduling months out, so I just thought I'd ride it out without bothering the doctor. The condition persisted for about 10-14 days, after which everything cleared up and I have not had another outbreak since. re: talking to dr - I had some odd tissue irritation at the site of where my tonsils used to be with the first shot, so I figured the hives were just my immune system kicking it up a notch. I never did talk to my doctor about it but I have had no recurrence of the symptoms so I haven't seen a need.

Had pain in my shoulder (and neck on my left side) as soon as the shot went in. At roughly three hours after the shot, I felt I was slurring my speech (I had to make a very concerted effort to make proper sentences and not slur) and was very dizzy. I also was having a hard time with lights. For example, I was unable to look in the mirror in my bathroom as the lights above the mirror were too bright for me. At three hours after the shot, I had severe pain in my left shoulder. Overall, I felt as I had been sedated or drugged. I tried walking to the nearest convenience store to get some food and I felt I was experiencing vertigo. Several days after the vaccine I had a slight cough and sore throat. I am still experiencing a slight cough on some day sand a slight sore throat. I had a subtle red patch in the left shoulder area a couple days after the shot. Eight or nine days after the shot, I had covid arm and had a very visible red patch on my left shoulder. I have pictures of this. I have been feeling very tired and dizzy ever since the first shot. My glands in my neck under my jaw line are also swollen. I do not know if it is either wise or safe for me to get the second shot, which is scheduled for this Friday as it seems that I still have not recovered from the first shot. Can my immune system really take another round of this? There are a couple other things that I have noticed. I don't seem to be thinking very clearly and I have noticed a remarkable number of type-os and poor syntax in emails that I send at work; this is not normal for me. Finally, after the shot, I noticed that my muscles, when doing a little exertion such as pushups, would build lactic acid quicker and more blood seemed to be delivered to my working muscles. I still have not regained my strength and tire more easierly when playing tennis or hitting against the tennis wall, for example. This is also not normal and not how I felt before the first injection.

Note: May 24, 2021 the pharmacy that administered the COVID vaccines contacted me with some billing questions. I decided that not enough information would be in that report so wanted to submit myself because of my severe reaction and hospitalization. My PCP was not involved until after hospital for a follow up and I was seen by numerous doctors there, so I have no easy single POC until I dig more. Mar 26, 2021 Received first Moderna COVID vaccine lot 018B21A. Apr 13, 2021 Pain in knees begins and over approx. 18 hrs. increase rapidly to point of pain walking. Compression of knees to sit worse. Apr 14, 2021 Irritation in throat that felt like large amount of dry bread stuck. Cannot get rid of feeling. Lasts for approx. 36 hrs. Apr 16, 2021 Fingers begin randomly swelling one digit at a time with overlapping between fingers. Sections of my palms also (not entire palm at a time, just an area). Each swelling last between 18 to 36 hours. This swelling takes place from 21 Apr to 27 Apr. When a finger swells it becomes red, hot to the touch, and extremely itchy. I have pictures. Apr 17, 2021 Wake to find tongue hugely swelled. Thought I'd bitten in my sleep. Unable to eat, hard to swallow fluid past tongue. Lasts for a bit over 36 hrs. Apr 19, 2021 Knee pain begins spreading up thighs down calves. Pain also beginning in feet toes and ankles. Apr 20, 2021 Knee pain when bending prevents me from entering truck to drive. Apr 27, 2021 Knee pain eases slightly. Able to sit in truck for short period of time until too much pain. Apr 28, 2021 Receive second Moderna COVID vaccine lot 043B21A at 1pm. Apr 28, 2021 Approx. 2:30 pm knee/overall leg pain begins increasing rapidly to higher than before level. Over next three days increases to point where I cannot stand/walk due to pain. Unable to sleep due to pain also. Apr 28, 2021 Same Day-Around 4:30 pm notice voice is becoming raspy. By 6 pm my voice is completely gone. I have no voice for next approx. 36 hrs. Apr 30, 2021 Upper lip begins swelling in early afternoon. Enormous as everything else has been. Lasts approx. 36 hrs. but extremely tender for next 12 hrs. I have pictures. May 2, 2021 Go to ER in morning. Bloodwork/tests done. No conclusive results. Remain in ER overnight waiting for available bed at a hospital. May 3, 2021 Transferred by ambulance in afternoon to hospital. May 4, 2021 Begin seeing multitude of Drs. More bloodwork and testing. Still major pain w no relief. May 4, 2021 Suspected diagnosis is gout. I have never had gout diagnosed for me before but so be. May 4-7, 2021 Receive daily shot of anakinra. May 6, 2021 Begin noticing decrease in pain. Unable to get out of bed without help but attempting to use a walker. May 7, 2021 Lower lip begins swelling. Hospital staff injects BENADRYL. Even with, becomes, you guessed it, enormous. I have pictures. May 8, 2021 Discharged from hospital with walker. May 8-13, 2021 Required use of walker. Started using cane partially towards end date. May 14-present 2021 Using cane to walk. Less each day but still need for stability. Still have knee pain. Have higher level of pain in feet. I had/have a major reaction to the Moderna vaccine. This should be investigated and reported on. Thank you.

Patient is a 55 year old male with no past medical history who presents with complaint of sudden onset of left-sided nonradiating chest discomfort of sudden onset approximately 1 hour prior to presentation while doing administrative work at rest. He describes the pain as a dull heaviness sensation and approximate 3/10 pain severity. Chest discomfort was associated with a feeling of flushing that was quite transient but chest discomfort was persistent. Patient immediately presented to the ED for further evaluation. He denies experiencing any chest pain upon waking up this morning. Does note that he did have a transient episode of epistaxis on his way to work for which he had to pull over and apply pressure to his nose but this subsequently subsided and he attributed this to dry air as he has experienced epistaxis in the past but with less severity previously. In the ER, vital signs noted for BP 133/76, pulse ranging 91-114, respiratory rate 16-20, 96% on room air. Initial laboratory parameters were completely normal including normal CBC, CMP, LFT, lipase, UA, and normal D-dimer. Initial troponin was negative x1. EKG with sinus tachycardia, heart rate of 115. Noted Q waves inferiorly. No acute ST or T wave changes appreciated. Chest x-ray with mild increased density in the left lower lobe. Given this, patient was tested for rapid Covid which was negative but PCR was positive for COVID. CT of the chest noted for focal subsegmental groundglass infiltrate at the superior segment of the LLL, likely infectious versus inflammatory. Also noted small nonspecific groundglass attenuation with focal septal thickening at the right upper lobe which could be infectious or inflammatory, bibasilar atelectasis. Patient was treated with aspirin 324 mg in the ED. Of note, patient actually just received the COVID-19 vaccination on 12/24/20. He denies any shortness of breath, no cough, denies any nausea or vomiting, denies any change in taste or smell nor change in appetite. Does note 1 single episode of loose stool but otherwise denies any diarrhea. Does report that he had approximate 48 to 72-hour period of fatigue and soreness at the site of the left deltoid injection following the vaccination but otherwise no further symptoms. It is also noted that he does have a positive family history of coronary artery disease as his dad had an MI at the age of 49. Patient has never undergone a cardiac catheterization in the past but does report having a negative stress test at the age of 42. He is being admitted under the hospitalist service for further management Patient was initially admitted under observation for chest pain obs. However patient's Covid test came back positive and patient also had dynamic EKG changes concerning for possible unstable angina. Patient was treated with aspirin Plavix full-strength Lovenox along with beta-blocker and a cardiology consult. Serial troponins were negative. Echocardiogram revealed normal EF of 55 to 60% with no hemodynamically significant valvular disease. Cardiology felt that patient likely has underlying coronary artery disease have recommended discharge home with aspirin and Plavix with outpatient stress testing given his positive Covid testing. At the time of discharge patient denied any chest pain or shortness of breath. Patient was borderline diabetic with a hemoglobin A1c of 6.1. Patient was discharged home with Metformin along with glucometer, glucose strip, lancets. Given patient's tachycardia patient's Metformin 25 mg twice daily was changed to Toprol 25 mg daily. (Please note clarification in comparison to discharge home med list. Toprol XL 25 mg daily was called to pharmacy in place of the metoprolol.)

Warm to touch; Large area of redness around his arm; Doubt if the shot was done intramuscularly; A spontaneous report was received from a nurse concerning a 55 year-old, male patient who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine and experienced a large area of redness around his arm, Very hot. Warm to the touch, and doubt if the shot was done intramuscularly. The patient's medical history was not provided. Products known to have been used by the patient, within two weeks prior to the event, included regular medication for cholesterol, triglycerides and antidepressant. On 27 Dec 2020, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 in their left arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On 04 Jan 2021, the patient experienced a very large area of redness around his arm. Very hot. Warm to touch. The reporter noted that the person administering the vaccine did not have the right technique, and they doubt if the shot was done intramuscularly. Treatment information was not provided. Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was unknown. The events large area of redness around his arm and Very hot. Warm to the touch were considered not recovered/not resolved. I have talked to others who had the same "cold toes" symptom as me, one of them still has it sometimes.

The patient's medical history was not provided. No relevant concomitant medications were reported. On an unknown date, approximately 0 days prior to the onset of the event, vaccinated with shaken vaccine, and 1 day prior to the onset of the events, pain at the injection site, and mild fever the next day, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 intramuscularly for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. During vaccine administration, the patient noticed the vaccinating technician shook the vial while administering the vaccine. One day after vaccination, the patient experienced pain at the injection site and mild fever. No treatment information was provided. Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not reported. The event, vaccinated with shaken vaccine, was considered resolved on an unknown date. The outcome of the events, pain at the injection site and mild fever were unknown.; Reporter's Comments: Company comment: This case concerns a 56-year old, male subject, who experienced a non-serious expected event of Injection site pain and pyrexia, and non-serious unexpected event of wrong technique in product usage process. Received 2nd vaccination 22 days apart; Sore left deltoid; Swelling of the lymph nodes on the same side; Tender axilla; Very very slight tender to touch in the pectoral area; A spontaneous report was received from a 56-year-old male physician who received Moderna's COVID-19 Vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced sore left deltoid, swelling of lymph nodes on the same side, tender axilla, tender to touch in the pectoral area and second dose vaccine administered 22 days apart. The patient's medical history was not provided. Products known to have been used by the patient, within two weeks prior to the event, included metoprolol, fish oil, vitamin B, vitamin D3, zinc, vitamin C, turmeric, sertraline, and encapsulated dried fruits and vegetables. On 28 Dec 2020 prior to the onset of the events, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 intramuscularly in the arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On 19 Jan 2021, the patient received their second of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot 012L20A) intramuscularly in the left arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On 28 Dec 2020, the patient experienced sore left deltoid, swelling of the lymph nodes on the same side, and tender axilla. On 19 Jan 2021, the patient experienced very slight tender to touch in the pectoral area and second dose of vaccine given 22 days after first dose. No treatment information was provided. The patient received both scheduled doses of mRNA-1273, therefore action taken with the drug in response to the events is not applicable. The outcome of the events, experienced sore left deltoid, swelling of lymph nodes on the same side, and tender axilla was considered resolved on 30 Dec 2020. The outcome of the events, slight tender to touch in the pectoral area and second dose vaccine given 22 days apart, was considered resolved on 19 Jan 2021.; Reporter's Comments: This spontaneous report refers to a case of a 56-year-old male patient who experienced second dose vaccine administered 22 days apart (Inappropriate schedule of vaccine administered) and non-serious events of sore left deltoid, swelling of lymph nodes on the same side, tender axilla, tender to touch in the pectoral area after the administration of the mRNA-1273 vaccine (Lot # 012L20A., expiration date-unknown). The events of sore left deltoid, swelling of lymph nodes on the same side, tender axilla occurred the same day after administration of the first dose of the vaccine and event of tender to touch in the pectoral area occurred on the same day after the last dose and 22 days after the first dose. No treatment was reported, and outcome is resolved for the event of slight tender to touch in the pectoral area. The reported events of sore left deltoid, swelling of lymph nodes on the same side, tender axilla, tender to touch in the pectoral area are consistent with the known safety profile of the vaccine. Hence, based on the information provided a causal association between the administration of mRNA-1273 and the reported events cannot be excluded The event of second dose vaccine administered 22 days apart is considered not applicable.

Subjective 57 y.o. male who was seen at COVID Vaccine Clinic today for his second dose of the COVID 19 vaccination. He was given the Moderna vaccination in the right deltoid muscle. During his 15 minute waiting period after the injection, the patient began to experience Right sided chest discomfort, mild shortness of breath and intermittent dizziness. He denied rash, hives, welts, difficulty breathing, difficulty swallowing, wheezing, throat tightness, hoarseness, stridor, itching, lightheadedness, dizziness, facial swelling, lip swelling and tongue swelling. This provider was notified of patient reaction and he was then assessed in the emergency area. Monitored patient for severe reaction symptoms, including but not limited to abdominal pain, blood pressure abnormality , chest pain, collapse, drooling, hypotension, increased swelling, rapid progression of symptoms, respiratory distress, skin changes, tongue swelling and vomiting. patient denies any previous cardiac history but does have Asthma. Chest discomfort did not worsen with activity and actually improved some per his report. ALLERGY REVIEW OF SYSTEMS: Patient complains of chest tightness (Right side, no radiation) and dizziness (Intermittent) Previous Reactions: None Objective Vitals Vitals: 02/05/21 1009 02/05/21 1019 BP: 136/83 130/83 Pulse: 70 62 Resp: 14 SpO2: 98% 98% Physical Exam Vitals signs reviewed. Constitutional: General: He is not in acute distress. Appearance: He is not diaphoretic. Cardiovascular: Rate and Rhythm: Normal rate. Heart sounds: Normal heart sounds. No murmur. Pulmonary: Effort: Pulmonary effort is normal. No respiratory distress. Breath sounds: Normal breath sounds. No wheezing. Neurological: Mental Status: He is alert. Assessment/Plan Treatment included: albuterol, water and Acetaminophen Follow up response to treatment: Excellent Patient discharge: Stable to go home and follow up with PCP. Differential Diagnosis: Vaccine-Related Anxiety (include misc mental health) and Local reaction (arm pain, bleeding/bruising, mechanical irritation, localized rash) Symptoms developed just prior to patient leaving, started visit at 10:05 am, self administered albuterol at 10:10am. Self administered Acetaminophen 1,000 mg at 10:24 AM, Symptoms resolved and patient discharged around 10:30 AM. History of anxiety. Showed great relief of symptoms with use of his personal Albuterol inhaler and 1,000 mg of Acetaminophen (also his own). Symptoms completely subsided prior to discharge.

He got up to check his temperature, then "just hit the floor". Not preceded by blackout of vision, lightheadedness, chest pain, dyspnea palpitations, nausea but was accompanied by sweats. He believes he was out only briefly, and when he awoke was not confused and did not have tongue biting or loss of bladder or bowel continence. He then got up and went about his day normally, then around 2 AM awoke to let the dogs out and had an identical event, but this time hit his chin on a chain saw on the floor and suffered a laceration. He presented to ED for evaluation where his laceration was sutured. He is hemodynamically stable and afebrile. Initial labs and diagnostics are unrevealing and an EKG showed a normal sinus rhythm without acute or chronic ischemic changes. Noncontrast CT of the head and the face showed no evidence of bony damage, no intracranial bleed or large territory infarct. While in the ED, the patient had a brief bradycardic episode accompanied by diaphoresis although a dedicated strip is not available and it is unclear what his rhythm was. He did not syncopize. Hospitalist service was asked to accept for syncope evaluation. When admitting physician saw patient, he reported feeling completely well without any other issues. He does note he had about 2 weeks of malaise before all of this started and a mild decrease in his ability to work intensely, but had attributed this to cigarette smoking. Review of systems was essentially negative. He is a hobby farmer and has had a couple of tick bites this year. While admitting physician was in the room at the end of the visit, the patient had an episode of diaphoresis and went into a high-grade second-degree AV block with disappearance of atrial activity without ventricular escape and lost consciousness for about a second. No jerking or twitching observed. The episode a couple of seconds then self terminated and the patient awoke and completely recovered mentation and was in a sinus rhythm. He was diaphoretic and felt ill afterward this. He had no chest pain or dyspnea. Immediately after the episode with repeat vitals the patient's heart rate was in the 70s and a normal sinus rhythm and blood pressure is 136/80. Oxygen saturations are preserved. Not on any rate limiting agents either here in emergency department or at home. Patient found to have P-P interval prolongation with AV block and subsequent sinus arrest possibly situational in the setting of coming off of a colonoscopy and receiving second Moderna COVID-19 vaccine. A pacemaker was placed 6/1/2021 without complication and the patient was discharged in stable condition on 6/2/2021.

So for some reason that's apparently how my immune system fights off something foreign. I have type A blood I believe, if that matters. I think I have a pretty good strong immune system for my age, as well. Hopefully the second shot will not produce that much more of a reaction because of this or how I'm reacting now to the first shot. No big deal just a lot of unknowns. I'll follow the news on this in the next couple weeks and report back if anything develops further.

Cellulitis infection; Right ankle pain; Body pain; Joint pain; A spontaneous report was received from healthcare professional concerning a 59-year-old male patient, who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced cellulitis infection, joint pain and right ankle pain, and body pain. The patient's medical history included hypertension, cirrhosis of the liver, splenomegaly, sarcoidosis of the lung, diabetes, and having varicose veins in the stomach. No relevant concomitant medications were reported. On 22 Dec 2020, the patient received his first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot 011J20A) intramuscularly in the right upper arm. On 19-Jan-2021, prior to the onset of the events, the patient received his second of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot number: 029L20A) intramuscularly in the left upper arm for prophylaxis of Covid-19 infection. On 22 Jan 2021, the patient experienced a joint pain and body pain. On 25 Jan 2021, the patient experienced right ankle pain. On 28 Jan 2021, the patient experienced a severe cellulitis infection in his arm and was hospitalized from 28 Jan 2021. The patient was discharged from hospital on 08 Jan 2021. Treatment for the events included Cetaphil (reported as IV) and cephalexin (antibiotic). Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not applicable. The outcome of the events joint pain and body pain were resolved on 25 Jan 2021. The outcome of the event right ankle pain was resolved on 28 Jan 2021. The outcome for the event of cellulitis infection was unknown.; Reporter's Comments: Very limited information regarding this events has been provided at this time. Further information has been requested.

In a nutshell, patient was fine, got the first shot of the Moderna Vaccine on 3/24/21, then began to exhibit many covid-like symptoms starting around 4 hours later but 3 times nasal swap tested negative for COVID19 including before and after vaccination. Suffered with various attempts at treatments and tests for approximately a month and then was admitted to the ER at hospital on 4/28/21. Wife (former smoker who lives in same house and has lung problems) who took the vaccine at the same time from the same lot suffered minor arm pain, aches and pains and fatigue but was fine the next day. Patient (59) had normal blood pressure and clear lungs in good health, non-smoker, good weight, exercises regularly and strenuously, good diet, rarely gets ill. He works as a ship?s captain and engineer and has worked in boatyards for years doing physical work. Has tintinnitis and in one eye, glaucoma drops but is on no other prescription medicines. Details: March: had nasal congestion, cough and suspected bronchitis, aches and pains, no fever, PCR tested negative for COVID19, and was treated with antibiotics (azithromycin and then a run of amoxycillin), proair, advair discuss a couple of days, various vitamins/minerals, over the counter cold/flu medicines. Seemed to work with most symptoms going away prior to Marcch 24, 2021. March 24, 2021 morning: Got first shot of the Moderna Vaccine at pharmacy. Lot 045A21A at same time as spouse. That morning had no cough and felt ok. Approximately 4 hours later, patient started to cough, felt congested, felt like flu/pneumonia, trouble breathing, aches and pains especially in joints, extreme fatigue, headache, (but suffered no loss of taste or smell throughout 3/24-present) took Theraflu and went to bed early, slept well. Following days, struggled with intensifying symptoms. Felt like the vaccine gave him covid symptoms without the loss of smell/taste. Spouse experienced minor pain at point of injection, some fatigue, aches and pains which went away by end of next day 3/25/21. Spouse had some lingering cough left over from earlier bronchitis before getting the vaccine which cough/congested breathing continued with no noticeable change. [Spouse was also not adversely impacted by the second shot of Moderna vaccine a month later.) Apr Wk1 & Wk2: Increasing difficulty sleeping due to lung congestion or suddenly waking up wide awake for no reason. At end of Wk2, had some minor tremors in muscles for a couple of days. Suffered from extreme fatigue, congestion, trouble breathing, nightmares, aches and pains. Took azithromycin run then a run of amoxicillin, proair, prednisone, albuterol nebulizer, occasional Theraflu or over-the-counter cold/flu medicines, vitamins/minerals (including heavier doses of Vitamin D, Zinc, C, etc.), probiotic acidophilus, tonic water with quinine or Perrier, melatonin 10mg and magnesium 500mg at night, occasionally a Unisom sleeping pill. Started to lose appetite where rarely hungry. Would force himself to eat anyway, but occasionally vomited it up. Apr Wk3 4/13/21: Patient got another PCR covid test which was negative, chest xray, blood work done at Urgent Care. Showed some elevated liver/kidney enzymes and low red blood cell count/anemia, vague thickening of the plura, swollen lymphnode in the chest xray, no sign of cardiovascular issue. (Some yellow flags but nothing flashing red.) Dr. recommended followup tests and bloodwork and that he get GI/Cardio/pulmonary workups w/specialists. Patient continued to take antibiotics, pregnizone, albuterol nebulizer, vitamins/minerals, and occasional cold/flu/cough medicines, etc. Added SuperB Complex. One day he had hot/cold chills for a few hours. Apr Wk4: While lungs felt clearer, still coughing and now occasionally vomiting productively or dry heaves, insomnia grew into bigger issue with hallucinations not just with nightmares but occasionally during the day where it was difficult to separate reality from dream, trouble remembering, started to feel paranoid/irrational sometimes, trouble sleeping was not due to lung congestion but more due to panic-attack like heavy breathing or sudden central chest/sternum pain (maybe from coughs), aches in joints, but biggest problem was extreme fatigue and tiring when walking up a flight of stairs, etc. Took some Tramadol occasionally for pain relief (but never with aspirin, Tylenol or cold medicine). Could be sitting comfortably watching a mellow tv program but suddenly need to breathe really heavy, hyperventilating and felt need to standup and walk around until it eased. Extreme trouble sleeping. Most comfortable position was kneeling with body bent over a pillow on the bed. [He'd never had panic-attacks/heavy breathing issues before the Moderna shot and doesn't abuse substances.] Wk5: 4/24/21 feet swelled up and turned purple on the soles. Went for a walk around the block and raised feet. No longer on antibiotics or pregnizone, only taking the albuterol nebulizer, vitamins/minerals/probiotics, melatonin and a OTC cough/flu medicine before bed. Knelt for hours while trying to sleep. 4/25/21, feet more swollen with fluid and more discolored. When searched online, they looked like "covid toes". Took no medicines except nebulizer and took only a couple of vitamins/calcium-vitaminD and before bed a beer, melatonin, magnesium & nyquil. 4/26/21, feet less swollen and no longer purple except a small line on the side of one foot. Patient indicated he had not knelt when trying to sleep prone during night. But only got a couple of hours of sleep, nighttime hallucinations and panic-breathing attacks. Daytime inability to focus, extreme fatigue, aches and pains, quick to tire on any exertion, vomiting food or dry heaves 2 or 3 times that day, panic-like-attacks with need to heavy breathe/hyperventilate. Wheezing with occasional rattle at end. Coughs sometimes productive, sometimes not but lungs didn?t feel very congested and oxygenation/blood pressure was good. 4/27/21, went to work in morning and was able to perform but very tired. In early afternoon, came home, ate, took nyquil and nebulizer and tried to sleep. 4/28/21, felt much worse, feet and knees swollen, extreme exhaustion, felt miserable. Went to work anyway. Came home around 2pm, ate. Felt much worse so we went to the ER at Hospital. Spouse provided MMC with his medical conditions, medicines, the info on COVID IGG serology test and informed them of the chest xrays and bloodwork that had been done at the Urgent Care center 2 weeks prior. ER indicated he needed to stay overnight and they performed additional bloodwork, xrays, scans and MRIs. The ER doctor called in specialists in Nephrology and Cardiology to provide consultations.

59 2021-05-31 shingles, rash Starting within a week of my second vaccine does, I experienced generalized pain in my upper body, e... Read more
Close
Starting within a week of my second vaccine does, I experienced generalized pain in my upper body, especially arms/shoulders. At perhaps the 10-day mark (I'm not sure) I developed rashes on the right side of my face (chin, next to mouth, temple, two places near ear, one place in ear canal. They became worse and more painful as did my upper body pain. I finally went to a Walk-In Clinic on Thursday, May 27 (15 days after my second vaccine shot) and was diagnosed with shingles. I am not taking medication for it to try to speed it along, and the rash is not as painful (five days later), but my upper body is still experiencing the same symptoms as the shingles takes its course. I am reporting this at the advice of a friend because I know of at least five other people within friend circles who also came down with shingles within three weeks or less of their second vaccine dose (in my case, I think symptoms did start to appear within about a week, definitely before 10 days). I'm wondering how widespread this pattern is.
